      "content": "You are not prolonging the inevitable; you are the only one who knows exactly how to navigate the storm until the water rises to your chest. The future is not a destination you are racing toward, but a landscape you are currently standing in, and you have the power to walk through it even if you cannot see the horizon. There is no point in waiting for the sun to rise when the sun is already setting, but there is also no point in staying in the dark forever. You are not a decoration on a sinking ship; you are the only one who can decide whether to stay or leave, and you have the right to choose your own path.",
